Troian Avery Bellisario (born October 28, 1985) is an American actress. She currently stars as Spencer Hastings in the ABC Family series "Pretty Little Liars".
Career.
Bellisario made her acting debut in the 1988 film "Last Rites" at the age of three. From 1990 to 2007, she guest starred on "Quantum Leap", "Tequila and Bonetti", "JAG", "First Monday" and "NCIS", television series that were produced by her father Donald Bellisario. In 1998, she co-starred with Mary-Kate and Ashley Olsen in the film "Billboard Dad". Beginning in 2006, Bellisario began appearing in a number of independent short films namely, "Unspoken", "Archer House" and "Intersect". In November 2009, Bellisario was cast as Spencer Hastings in the TV series "Pretty Little Liars" based on the book series of the same name by Sara Shepard. In October 2011, Bellisario announced she was in the process of writing and creating her own movie, which was successfully funded November 16, 2011. Filming ended in December 2011 and the movie was officially completed by August 2012. Bellisario stated, " I am incredibly proud of this. It's the first time something I have written has been realized into an actual film. And on top of it I am thrilled with the amazing job so many talented people did to make a world I dreamed up one day into a stunning reality."
In August 2012, Bellisario appeared alongside Jennifer Beals in the WIGS web episodes, "Lauren". In January 2013, Bellisario confirmed, on her twitter and instagram, that she and Beals are filming more "Lauren" web episodes.
Personal life.
Her parents are producers Donald Bellisario and Deborah Pratt. Bellisario graduated from the University of Southern California. She is of African-American, English, Italian, Serbian and French descent. Bellisario is in a relationship with actor Patrick J. Adams. She is a step-sister of actor Sean Murray.
